post_text: As the safety of our students and staff continues to be a top priority, decisions have been made to implement some significant measures to enhance the security of our campus. First, beginning February 24th (the last week of the month) we will begin to utilize a new system for guest management. All guests entering the building during the school day will need to sign in by scanning a state-issued driver’s license/ID. After the license scan the system will generate a sticker/pass with your picture, allowing students and staff to more easily recognize guests. The ID scan will occur whether you are there to simply to sign students out or visit students and/or classrooms. You may read more detail about the Visitor Management system in the “district news” section of our school website

Makeup Day Notification
Potential makeup days to be scheduled in the event that we exceed 5 full calamity/cancellation days due to bad weather or other unforeseen circumstances.

IF 6 or more calamity days are accumulated by Friday, 1/31/20:
-The February staff development day (2/14/20) and/or Presidents’ Day (2/17/20) will be scheduled as regular instructional day(s).

IF 6 or more calamity days are accumulated by Friday, 3/6/20:
-The March staff development day (3/16/20) will be scheduled as a regular instructional day.

post_text:
Elgin Alumni Association offers annual scholarships to Elgin High School seniors or graduates. Criteria for the Elgin Alumni Association Scholarship and the Cheryl Oehler Memorial Scholarship can be found at the Marion Community Foundation Scholarship Program webpage.

One application makes students eligible for all scholarships for which they qualify. Only online applications will be accepted. The application does require recommendations, essays, financial information, and more. Submitting FAFSA information is optional but highly recommended. We encourage students to start early so these time-consuming items can be completed.

The online application can be found at: www.MarionCommunityFoundation.org.

DEADLINE is Friday, February 28, 2020, at 12:00 p.m. (noon)

post_text:
Did you know that a significant percentage of college admissions counselors will try to review your child’s social media platforms? What will they find if they look?
Did you know that your children are at risk of going to prison and being listed on a sexual predator registry because of the photos they are sending AND receiving on their smartphones?
Did you know that high school juniors and seniors are routinely getting their college acceptances and scholarships revoked for less than honorable social platform behavior?
If you had to sum up your child’s online reputation into a sentence what would it be? Do you even know?
If any of these surprised you, come and learn more at the Internet Safety for Parents presentation….

post_text:
Is your 11-18 year old using TikTok or SnapChat? Do you even know what these platforms are meant to do? (Spoiler alert: neither one of these apps should exist anywhere in your home)
Are you aware that the overwhelming percentage of children are regular consumers of online pornography? And by the way, they don’t think it’s a big deal.
Did you know that your tweens and teens are regularly making it incredibly easy for sexual predators and “cyberbullies” to stalk them?
Did you know that chances are that your child has been the cyberbully at least a couple of times?
If any of these surprised you, come and learn more at the Internet Safety for Parents presentation.....

Do you hand your child your iPad or smartphone to 'play with'?
Do you understand the sexual predation risks associated with your child playing otherwise benign games like Clash of Clans or Words with Friends?
Do you realize that your very young children (ages 6-10) have probably already been exposed to online pornography?
If any of these surprised you, come and learn more at the Internet Safety for Parents presentation on October 8 at 6pm in the Elgin?

post_text:
Immunizations - Next Year's 7th Graders

Attention parents of all current 6th grade students:

Ohio law dictates that all 2014-15 incoming 7th graders must receive a Tdap vaccination before entering school in the fall.

Please make an appointment with your health care provider soon as these slots generally fill very quickly in the late summer.

Your child will be excluded from attending school if he/she does not have this mandatory immunization.

If you have any questions pleae feel free to call the Marion Public Health Department at 740-387-6520 or Mrs. Ute at 740-223-4300

Elgin Fellowship of Christian Athletes are hosting a 5K run "Leave the Devil in the Dust" on Saturday April 12th. The Registration time is 8am and start time is 9am at Marion Catholic High School parking lot.
To register please visit www.elginschools.org. In the news sections of our website you will find more race information, specifically, registration, sponsorship opportunities and the race route. Please contact Mr. Curtis at Elgin Middle/High School (740) 223-4300 if you have any further questions. The entry fee is $25, but if you donate five (5) pairs of new or gently used flip flops, it will be reduced to $20. You will receive a t-shirt, and if we run out we will mail one to you. EVERYONE IS WELCOME!

post_text: The Jobs for America's Graduates program is a facilitating a shoe and clothing drive through the Soles for Souls organization. J.A.G. students will have collection bins setup in different areas of the building for clothing and shoe collections. We will be collecting these items through April 1st. Considering that spring is almost here, students thought that this would be a great time to take a look in your closets and find any unwanted shoes or clothing and donate it to a great cause. If you are interested in learning more about the organization Soles for Souls, please take a moment and check out their website, http://soles4souls.org. Please contact Mr. Drew Kirby with any questions.

post_text: Elgin High School along with many of Elgin Local's student leadership groups are collecting new or used flip flops. All of the collected flip flops will be donated to children of all ages all around the world that are without shoes. Elgin's Fellowship of Christians recently partnered with Flip Flop Around The World. The mission of Flip Flop Around The World is: To send donations of new and gently used flip flops to people in need in developing and third world countries. Student leadership groups throughout the entire building are working to donate to this cause. Please contact Mr. Curtis if you are interested in getting involved.

post_text:
EHS Presents "The Sound of Music"
Elgin High School is pleased to announce our 2014 Spring Musical. On April 11th, 12th, and 13th the students of Elgin High School, under the direction of Miss Natalie Bowsher, will be performing "The Sound of Music". Auditions will be held in early February, and tickets will go on sale in early to mid-March. The shows Friday (4/11) and Saturday (4/12) will begin at 7:00 PM, with a dinner theater option on Saturday night at 6:00 PM. Sunday afternoon's matinee will begin at 2:00 PM. Please mark your calendars now, and plan on joining us for one of the performances.

post_text: Elgin students involved in FCA are collecting toys for donation. Anyone that donates a toy or toys will receive one ticket for free admission to an Elgin athletic event. Toys are being collected through next week and are due before December 19th 2013. If you have any questions please call 740-223-4300 and ask to speak to Mr. Curtis or email at curtis_s@elginschools.org.
